casebody.data:
Johnny KITTRELL, Respondent,
v.
TOWNSEND TREE SERVICE, Appellant. No. ED 106390 Missouri Court of Appeals, Eastern District, DIVISION THREE. Filed: October 2, 2018 Daniel J. Walkenhorst, 906 Olive Street, Suite 400, St. Louis, MO 63101, For Respondent. William Lemp, 8045 Big Bend Blvd., Suite 202, Webster Groves, MO 63119, For Appellant. Before Sherri B. Sullivan, P.J., Lawrence E. Mooney, J., and James M. Dowd, J.

ORDER

PER CURIAM.

In this worker's compensation case, Townsend Tree Service appeals the decision of the Labor and Industrial Relations Commission awarding permanent and total disability benefits to claimant Johnny Kittrell. An opinion would have no precedential value. We have furnished the parties with a memorandum, for their information only, setting forth the reasons for our decision. We affirm. Rule 84.16(b)(4).
